    "en": {
      "title": "Ministers go abroad to find solutions to crisis",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Several ministers left the Katunayake airport on the night of 06/27 and the morning of 06/28 in search of a solution to the fuel crisis in Sri Lanka.",
        "Accordingly, the Minister of Energy Kanchana Wijesekera has left for Qatar on the night of 06/27. The Minister had left Doha, Qatar on a Qatar Airways flight QR-655 on 08/27 at 08.15 pm from the Katunayake Airport.",
        "He was accompanied by Environment Minister Nasir Ahmed on the same flight to Doha, Qatar. They are scheduled to visit Qatar to find a regular fuel supplier.",
        "In addition, Minister Susil Premajayantha has left for Dubai on the morning of 06/28 to leave for France. He had left Dubai for Katunayake on 06/28 at 03.15 am on an Emirates flight EK-649.",
        "A delegation including Minister Susil Premajayantha and former Sri Lankan Ambassador to Russia Dr. Saman Weerasinghe is scheduled to leave for Moscow, Russia on July 3 to find a solution to the fuel crisis."
      ],
